Grammy nominations: Michael Daugherty, Steve Mackey lead in the classical period categories 
The classical period nominations for the 53rd Grammy-Award contain a coloured mix in musicians and composers from all over the world. 
The list is stated by Michael Daughertys "Deux of ex Machina" for piano and orchestra with five voices, and Steve Mackeys "Dreamhouse," to an eclectic orchestra work, with three voices. 
Among the nominated with connections to South California the Estonian composer Arvo Pärt with his symphony is No. 4 "Los Angeles." This piece was ordered by Los Angeles to members of a philharmonic orchestra and was performed for the first time in 2009 in Walt Disney Concert Hall. 
The composer Avner Dorman resident in L.A. was also nominated for his mandolin concert. 
Classical period nominations are split in 13 categories, by orchestra, opera, choir up to solo admissions. 
In the category of the classical period producers five artists were nominated this year - Blanton Alspaugh, David Frost, Tim Handley, Marina and Victor Ledin and James Mallinson. 
Unter den nominierten Klassik-Alben sind Bruckners Symphonien Nr. 3 und 4 vom Royal Concertgebouw Orchestrated; Daughertys "deus ex machina " und " Metropolis Symphony " gespielt vom Nashville Symphony Orchestra; Steven Mackeys " Dreamhouse " vom Boston Modern Orchestra Project and Synergy Vocals; "Sacrificium - the Art of the Castrati" vorgetragen von verschiedenen Künstlern; und Verdi' s "requiem " vom Chicago Symphony Orchestra und Chor. 
In der Opernkategorie wurden Eisberge "Lulu vom Opernhaus von Orchester des Royal; Adolf Hasses "Marc Antonio e Cleopatra" von Ars Lyrica Houston; Kaija Saariahos "L'Amour de Loin" vom Deutschen Symphonie-Orchester Berlin; Rodion Shchedrins "Der Verzauberte Wanderer" vom Orchester und Theater von Chor des Mariinsky; und Arthur Sullivans "Ivanhoe" vom BBC Nationales Orchester Wales nominiert. 
As composers Pärt were nominated for symphony No. 4, Daugherty for "Deus of ex Machina," Hans Werner Henze for "Appassionatamente of plus," Magnus Lindberg for "graffiti" and Shchedrin for "The Enchanted of traveller" for a Grammy. 
Pärts symphony No. 4 was performed for the first time on the 4th of January in Disney sound by L.A. to members of a philharmonic orchestra under the direction of Esa-Pekka Salonen and was taped. 
The approx. 30-minute piece carries the title "Los Angeles" and is to the former oil magnate Mikhail Chodorkowski gewidmen who sits in Russia in the prison. 
Dormans "Mondolinenkonzert" received a nomination in the category Instrumental-solo with orchestra. 
The composer from L.A. bragged, he has written the 15-minute piece especially for the mandolin artist Avi Avital who performed the concert with the New York Metropolis ensemble. 
"I have used sounds from the Middle East and numerous North-African tones and rhythms," explained Dorman during a phone interview. 
The conductor Pierre Boulez, 85, received a nomination in the category Orchestra presentation for an admission of the works Strawinskis with Chicago symphony orchestra under his management. 
Als Instrumentalsolisten wurden die Pianisten Nelson Freire und Marc-André Hamelin, der Organist Paul Jacobs, die Geigerin Julia Fischer und nominiert die Harfinistin Sarah Schuster Ericsson. 
As solo singers only women were nominated this year, under it Anne Sofie von Otter, Cecilia Bartoli, Lucia Duchonová, Vivica Genaux and Measha Brueggergosman. 
In the category Classical period crossover the soprano Jessye Norman became for her admission "Roots - micron Life, micron of song" nominated. 
